OL,3,C'Clifton Rapist' Ronald Evans will
OL,4,Cstay in prison
OL,6,FHis probation officer noted Mr Evans'
OL,7,Fcomplacency during the time spent in
OL,8,Fthe community before this, agreed that
OL,9,Fhe could not safely be allocated to
OL,10,Fopen prison at this stage.
OL,12,FA spokesperson for the parole board
OL,13,Fsaid: "After considering the
OL,14,Fcircumstances of his offending, the
OL,15,Fprogress made while in custody, his
OL,16,Fbehaviour on licence, and the other
OL,17,Fevidence presented at the hearing, the
OL,18,Fpanel did not recommend to the
OL,19,FSecretary of State that Mr Evans
OL,20,Fshould be transferred to open prison.
